{
  "case_id": "D2N092",
  "method": "medsum_ent",
  "template": "soap",
  "summary_text": "S:\nThe patient reports pain in his distal radius following a tennis injury, specifically after hitting the net with the top of the racquet. He describes some numbness in his hand with wrist movement, but denies numbness in his hand. He reports a small amount of swelling, but not significant. The patient's past medical history includes allergies and he takes flonase. He reports a history of trauma from falling while doing lawn work. He states he had a stabbing injury to his arm.\n\nO:\nThe physical exam reveals tenderness to palpation over the distal radius, exacerbated by pressure and flexion. Tenderness is also noted with thumb flexion. The x-ray demonstrates no fractures or significant abnormalities. There is no evidence of gross swelling.\n\nA:\nThe patient's symptoms are consistent with a strain and contusion of the muscle in the distal radius. There is no fracture detected on the x-ray.\n\nP:\nI am prescribing motrin 800 milligrams three times a day with food for 7 days. I recommend ice packs to the affected area for 20 minutes every 2-3 hours. Follow up in one week if symptoms do not improve or worsen. Dragon, please order the medications and schedule a follow-up appointment.",
  "reference_summary": "CC:\n\nRight arm pain.\n\nHPI:\n\nMs. Martinez is a 43-year-old female who presents today for an evaluation of right arm pain after she hitting her arm on a pole while playing tennis. She had mild swelling at the time. There is pain with motion. She denies any numbness or tingling in her hand. She has a past medical history of allergies and takes Flonase.\n\nEXAM\n\nExamination of the left wrist shows tenderness over the distal radius and pain with flexion of the wrist and thumb.\n\nRESULTS\n\nX-rays of the left wrist show no obvious signs of acute fracture or other abnormality.\n\nIMPRESSION\n\nRight wrist sprain.\n\nPLAN\n\nAt this point, I discussed the diagnosis and treatment options with the patient. I have recommended ice and anti-inflammatory medications. I am prescribing Motrin, 800 mg to take 3 times a day with food. She will follow up with me in 1 week or as needed.",
